description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rush Hill &amp; Weston Surgeries&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bath&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BA2 2QH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salaried GP for up to 6 x sessions per week. Happy to consider applications for less than 6 sessions per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly and supportive training practice looking for a salaried GP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We love being GP&#39;s and our core value is to provide high quality and continuity of care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The practice is very proud and privileged to receive excellent feedback about the quality of the service that we provide to our patients. We have a current list size of just under 8000 patients and we are growing steadily.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have excellent working relationships with other local practices and work very collaboratively with our colleagues as part of the Minerva Primary Care Network (Minerva PCN).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TPP Systmone clinical system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accrx&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great dedicated clinical and administrative support team, including an excellent Specialist Paramedic for acute care alongside a very experienced and skilled nursing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly skilled, well established pharmacy team and Social Prescriber working across our PCN and a highly effective MDT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training practice and regularly have GP registrars and student nurses and mentorship for non- medical prescribers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Are We Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Someone who loves being a GP and who wants to provide excellent clinical care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;6 x sessions per week - Some flexibility over days, but preferably to include a Friday. Primarily at Rush Hill site with 1-2 session at our Combe Park site per week (based on a 6 session week).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
